# SUMMARY-complex.md Template

<!-- Downstream consumers:
  - check-plan-format.js (validateSummary): validates frontmatter fields (phase, plan, status, provides, requires, key_files). Does NOT validate body sections.
  - Status skill: reads plan completion status and metrics. Needs: frontmatter status field, metrics block.
  - Dashboard: displays plan details and accomplishments. Needs: frontmatter + body structure.
  Breaks if missing: Validator rejects summary without required frontmatter; status skill cannot track completion; dashboard shows empty plan card.
-->

> Use when: decisions were made OR fileCount > 6
> Referenced by: executor agent (complex plans, architectural work)

## Frontmatter (YAML)

```yaml
---
phase: "{phase_id}"
plan: "{plan_id}"
status: "complete"           # complete | partial | checkpoint
subsystem: "{main subsystem affected}"
tags:
  - "{tag1}"
requires:
  - "{plan_id}: {artifact}"
provides:
  - "{export/artifact description}"
affects:
  - "{affected area 1}"
tech_stack:
  - "{technology used}"
key_files:
  - "{file1}: {what it does}"
key_decisions:
  - "{decision 1}: {rationale}"
patterns:
  - "{pattern used}: {where}"
metrics:
  duration_minutes: {n}
  tasks_completed: {n}
  tasks_total: {n}
  commits: {n}
  files_created: {n}
  files_modified: {n}
requirements_completed:
  - "REQ-ID: brief description of how it was satisfied"
deviations:
  - rule: 1          # 1=Bug, 2=Missing Critical, 3=Blocking, 4=Architectural
    description: "..."
    action: "auto"   # auto | ask
    justification: "..."
deferred:
  - "{thing noticed but not implemented}"
self_check_failures:
  - "{failure description}"
architecture_notes:
  - "{key architectural decision and why}"
---
```

## Body Structure

```markdown
# Plan Summary: {plan_id}

## What Was Built

{2-3 paragraph description of what was accomplished}

## Architecture Decisions

| Decision | Options Considered | Chosen | Rationale |
|----------|-------------------|--------|-----------|
| {decision} | {opt1}, {opt2} | {chosen} | {why} |

## Task Results

| Task | Status | Commit | Files | Verify |
|------|--------|--------|-------|--------|
| {task_id}: {name} | done | {hash} | {count} | passed |

## Key Implementation Details

{Important details about HOW things were implemented}

## Integration Points

{How this plan connects to other plans - imports, exports, shared state}

## Known Issues

{Issues discovered during execution}

## Dependencies Provided

{What other plans can now depend on}

## Deviations

| # | Rule | Description | Action | Justification |
|---|------|-------------|--------|---------------|
| 1 | Rule 1 (Bug) | {description} | auto | {why} |

## Self-Check

- [ ] All tasks completed per plan
- [ ] Commits match task count
- [ ] No TODO/FIXME left in new code
- [ ] Key files exist and are substantive
- [ ] requirements_completed matches plan implements

## Deferred Items

{Items noticed but intentionally deferred - with rationale}

## Quality Criteria

A good plan summary satisfies:
- [ ] All frontmatter fields are populated (no empty or placeholder values)
- [ ] key_files paths reference files that exist in the repository
- [ ] What Was Built section describes concrete outcomes, not process
- [ ] Architecture Decisions table documents any deviations from the plan
- [ ] Task Results table has a row for every task in the plan
- [ ] Deferred Items section explains rationale for each deferral
```

## Selection Heuristic

Use this template when ANY of the following are true:
- Key architectural decisions were made during execution
- Total files created or modified > 6
- Deviations from the plan occurred
- Multiple integration points were established
- The plan touched shared infrastructure or patterns
